      • logDisplayFailure

        public boolean logDisplayFailure(InAppMessageFailureType failureType)
        Description copied from interface: IInAppMessage
        Logs a display failure on this in-app message. Failures can only be logged once per in-app message instance and should be logged as early as possible in the display process. In-app message display failures may affect campaign statistics so care should be taken when logging display failures.
        Specified by:
        logDisplayFailure in interface IInAppMessage
        Parameters:
        failureType - The precise type of the display failure.
        Returns:
        true if the display failure was successfully logged.

      • forJsonPut

        public org.json.JSONObject forJsonPut()
        Storing in-app messages serialized with this method is primarily for storage as triggered actions. This allows in-app messages to be stored to disk and retrieved later for display when an in-app message triggered action is triggered.
        Specified by:
        forJsonPut in interface IPutIntoJson<org.json.JSONObject>
        Returns:
        a JSON representation of this in-app message sufficient for restoring it as a triggered action.
